body:
On which platform did you see this? If it is on Windows or Linux you can try generating stack trace by disabling crash-reporter and setting the `ELECTRON_ENABLE_STACK_DUMPING` env:

```
env ELECTRON_ENABLE_STACK_DUMPING=1 electron
```
It is on Mac where I saw it. I was acessing an undefined property (something.length where something was null) from the callback in makeSingleInstance. I can try to find the stackdump.

I just succeeded to reproduce by calling:

``` js
var shouldQuit = app.makeSingleInstance(function() {
  throw new Error;
});
```
